data.text: The rate or a measure of the rate of motion, especially.
data.attributionText: from The American Heritage® Dictionary of the English Language, 5th Edition.

data.text: Distance traveled divided by the time of travel.
data.attributionText: from The American Heritage® Dictionary of the English Language, 5th Edition.

data.text: The limit of this quotient as the time of travel becomes vanishingly small; the first derivative of distance with respect to time.
data.attributionText: from The American Heritage® Dictionary of the English Language, 5th Edition.

data.text: The state of being in rapid motion; rapidity.
data.attributionText: from The American Heritage® Dictionary of the English Language, 5th Edition.
examples: The river's speed made a rescue difficult.

data.text: A transmission gear or set of gears in a motor vehicle.
data.attributionText: from The American Heritage® Dictionary of the English Language, 5th Edition.
examples: What speed is the car in now?
